                "caption": "Figure 2:Comparison of Transport Maps on Synthetic Manifolds.We evaluateActAdd,Linear-ACT, andourMLP Transportagainst the Safe Target (Green).(1) Simple Gaussian:All methods successfully align with the target.(2) Variance Mismatch:ActAddfails to rotate the distribution whileLinear-ACTcompresses the variance into a thin line.MLPmatches the target geometry.(3) The Moon:Linear-ACTshrinks the crescent into the target distribution range but fails to unbend the topology.MLPmorphs the shape correctly.(4) Multi-Modal XOR:Global linear methods scatter clusters due to conflicting directions.MLP Transportcorrectly maps each cluster to its local target.",
